HEADWORD: Flipper
<hw>Flip"per</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Flip</er>,
<er>Flippant</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A broad
flat limb used for swimming, as those of seals, sea turtles, whales,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
